#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:149
msgid "KleverNotes 1.1.0 is finally available! KleverNotes is the Markdown note-taking app from KDE. For 3 months, I have been working hard to add new features while improving the app and fixing some bugs."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:154
msgid "KleverNotes parser has been switched to md4qt:"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:155
msgid "md4qt is a header-only C++ library for parsing Markdown."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:156
msgid "md4qt supports CommonMark 0.31.2 Spec, and some GitHub extensions, such as tables, footnotes, tasks lists, strikethroughs, LaTeX Math injections, GitHub's autolinks."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:161
msgid "It is fast, repliable, customizable and easy to use. A perfect match !"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:162
msgid "The toolbar is now more precise for removing specific Markdown tags but also to apply them."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:163
msgid "On top of that, the toolbar now shows you which tags are already applied on the text under the cursor or the selected text."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:164
msgid "The editor has also gained some interesting features. Block tab/untab support and automatic addition of list items are now more reliable, but you now also have the ability to add an html break before a new line with `Shift + Enter` or a horizontal ruler using `Alt + Enter`."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: ul/li
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:171
msgid "The parsing is now done on a separated thread, so parsing very large notes should still be smooth !"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: ul/li
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:172
msgid "The rendering is now disabled if the preview is disabled, saving some resources !"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: ul/li
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:173
msgid "Using the toolbar will now add or remove text in a single undo block, no more double/triple `Ctrl+Z` to go back to your previous state."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:175
msgid "The editor now has the ability to be \"WYSIWYG\"."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:176
msgid "By default, the markdown tags will be smaller than the rest of text by 50%, this can of course be tweaked in the settings."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:177
msgid "Those tags will regain their normal sizes based on the cursor position/selected text. This way, you're able to see which tag is responsible for a style."
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:182
msgid "KleverNotes, KDE's Markdown note-taking and management application using Kirigami, is ready for its first release!"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:185
msgid "KleverNotes allows you to create and preview a Markdown note while giving you the freedom to customize the preview from settings or using a CSS theme. You can organize your notes however you want with a combination of categories and groups, which will be directly reflected on your system in the hierarchy of your KleverNotes storage folders. Simply choose your storage location and you're ready to write!"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:191
msgid "You can print your notes, add small sketches and even create specific tasks for each of them, all from the application!"
msgstr ""

#. (itstool) path: description/p
#: org.kde.klevernotes.metainfo.xml:194
msgid "Notes are saved as Markdown files in your KleverNotes storage for easy access. They support the entire CommonMark specification with extensive syntax. KleverNotes also introduces a small collection of opt-in “plugins” to extend basic markdown features, such as: code highlighting, note linking, quick emoji, etc."
msgstr ""
